CBRE, as the exclusive listing agents, are pleased to present 89 Park Road, Auburn. This rare 612sqm* corner block is the first offering in over 100 years and includes lease. Sitting on a R3 Medium Density Residential zoned block, the site provides savvy investors with various potential future options; with the ability to occupy, invest or develop.

Fronting both Park and Union Road, buyers will appreciate the convenient location of the block; sitting within close proximity to a wide-variety of useful amenities, shops, restaurants, public transport options and specialty stores. 


The major arterial road of St Hilliers, which is located a mere 5-minute* drive connects commuters to Parramatta Road and more importantly, the Western Motorway (M4), allowing East and West-bound travel across Sydney. 

89 Park Road, Auburn benefits from the following key attributes:
- Corner block with lease
- Current three (3) year tenancy schedule of $54,185.50 ending April 2021
- New three (3) year tenancy schedule of $55,293,72 + CPI ending April 2024
- Leased to Sand4U, provider of landscape supplies
- Statutory Outgoings:
   - Council Rates: $2,269.15
   - Water Rates: $100.32 plus water usage
   - Total Outgoings: 100% of outgoings payable by the lessee as set out in the lease
- Site area of approx. 612sqm*
- Zoned on a R3 Medium Density Residential block
- Deceased Estate
- Moments to public transport options and major arterial roads

89 Park Road, Auburn will be sold via a Public Auction on the 23rd of March 2021 at 10:30am at Mezzanine Level, 
50 Margaret Street, Sydney NSW 2000 (Livestream and Online Bidding Available)

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as exclusive selling agents, is delighted to present for the first time in over forty years, 218-220 Parramatta Rd, Auburn; a freestanding building with exceptional Parramatta Road exposure. 

218-220 Parramatta Road presents a rare opportunity for owner occupiers, investors and developers to acquire a freestanding building along the Parramatta Road corridor. The property is less than 1km to the M4 on/off ramp. (20.1km west of CBD approx.). Walking distance to Auburn railway station & bus stop which is located at the front of the property. Close vicinity to all essential amenities.

This property will attract many buyers because of its many key attributes, including:

- First time offered to market in 40 years
- Land Area: 1,490sqm*
- Building Area: 788sqm*
- Clear-span warehouse reaching 6.5m*
- Access via one (1) roller shutter door
- Quality ground floor showroom area
- Huge signage potential
- 3 phase power supply
- Offered with vacant possession
- Numerous value-add possibilities
- Full brick construction
- Roof was replaced (approximately) 18 years ago

Arguably the busiest commercial enterprise hub in the Sydney Metropolitan region with over 22,000 cars passing daily. Within 2.5km of the new Carter St residential precinct, 3,500 apartments to be built in the next 3 years which will increase vehicle numbers along Parramatta Road. Auburn is a major inner west growth suburb within Metropolitan Sydney. The property is located within the main bulky goods retail district of Auburn on Parramatta Road, which accommodates national and international brand heavy weights including: Costco, Harvey Norman, Bunnings Warehouse, Fantastic Furniture, Adidas & Nike.


For a copy of the Executive Summary or to arrange an inspection, contact the exclusive selling agent today.
